From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000011 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Boot Debug <noreply@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [DEV] linux-qcom-6.18: disable PCIe1 on Lemans/Monaco (boot time)

On IQ-9075 (Lemans) / IQ-8275 (Monaco) EVK with an UNPOPULATED PCIe1 slot,
the PCIe driver probe spends ~600ms waiting for link training on the empty
slot, blocking the boot critical path. Production boards populate the slot,
but for QuickBoot / boot-time work with an empty slot this is a large,
avoidable delay.

Adds a kernel DTS patch (0001-linux-qcom-6.18-disable-PCIe1-controller-and-
PHY-on.patch) that sets pcie1 + pcie1_phy status="disabled" in lemans-evk.dts,
lemans-ride-common.dtsi, monaco-evk-common.dtsi and qcs8300-ride.dts, and
wires it into the linux-qcom_6.18 recipe SRC_URI. Recovers ~600ms of kernel
boot time.

NOTE: re-enable PCIe1 (drop this entry from local-patches.yml) if the PCIe1
slot is populated on the target board.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [PCIe hack to prevent 0.6s boot blocker]
---
diff --git a/recipes-kernel/linux/linux-qcom-6.18/0001-linux-qcom-6.18-disable-PCIe1-controller-and-PHY-on.patch b/recipes-kernel/linux/linux-qcom-6.18/0001-linux-qcom-6.18-disable-PCIe1-controller-and-PHY-on.patch
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..e609f859
--- /dev/null
+++ b/recipes-kernel/linux/linux-qcom-6.18/0001-linux-qcom-6.18-disable-PCIe1-controller-and-PHY-on.patch
@@ -0,0 +1,111 @@
+From fb8c7d16d7e877562187c4e751bd72f4952da23b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: Ziyue Zhang <ziyue.zhang@oss.qualcomm.com>
+Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 12:44:54 +0530
+Subject: [DO NOT MERGE] arm64: dts: qcom: lemans: monaco: disable PCIe1
+ controller and PHY
+
+PCIe1 to be not used on Lemans, Monaco-based platforms.
+
+Disable the PCIe1 controller and its associated PHY in both the shared
+Ride common DTSI and the EVK board DTS to prevent unnecessary resource
+allocation and avoid spurious probe failures.
+
+Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [PCIe hack to prevent 0.6s blocker in
+boot time]
+Signed-off-by: Ziyue Zhang <ziyue.zhang@oss.qualcomm.com>
